body:
The generated 2D filterbank includes filters that are not used in the computation.

Let's create a scattering transform:
```
>>> import kymatio
>>> s = kymatio.Scattering2D(J=2, shape=(32, 32))
```

Let's look at the shapes of the generated filters:
```
>>> print("\n".join('{' + ', '.join('%s: %s' % (k, getattr(v, 'shape', v)) for k, v in psi.items()) + '}' for psi in s.Psi))
{j: 0, theta: 0, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 1, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 2, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 3, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 4, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 5, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 6, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 0, theta: 7, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 0, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 1, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 2, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 3, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 4, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 5, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 6, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
{j: 1, theta: 7, 0: torch.Size([40, 40, 2]), 1: torch.Size([20, 20, 2])}
```

The 20x20 filters are all unused. Demonstration:
```
>>> for p in s.Psi:
...     if 1 in p:
...        p[1] = 'foo'
...
>>> import torch
>>> x = torch.rand((1, 1, 32, 32)).cuda()
>>> s = s.cuda()
>>> y = s(x)
```

They should probably not be part of the filterbank in the first place?
